title: okonomiyaki

needs:
 - 40g flour
 - 1 egg
 - soy sauce
 - Worcestershire sauce
 - 50g finely shredded cabbage
 - 2-3 finely sliced scallions
 - optional fillings (e.g. fried mushrooms & tofu)
 - optional mayo

steps:
 - mix the flour and egg until a smooth paste.
 - stir in the Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce.
 - turn the cabbage and one of the scallions into the mixture.
 - turn any fillings into the mixture.
 - thin the batter with water if needed.
 - fry for about 5 minutes on each side.
 - serve with a drizzle of mayo on top, topped with the remaining scallions.
